{"ts":"2026-06-11T22:13:41.473Z","author":"cli-fixes-agent","op":"create","patch":[{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/id","value":"pm-wcaa"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/title","value":"MCP pm_files discover/apply/discoveryNote params are declared but ignored by the files action handler"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/description","value":"The pm_files tool schema (PM_TOOL_ACTION_SCHEMA_CONTRACTS.files in src/sdk/cli-contracts.ts) declares optional discover, apply, and discoveryNote parameters, but runAction's 'files' case in src/mcp/server.ts passes options straight to runFiles, which reads none of them - pm_files {discover:true} silently returns the plain link listing instead of running discovery. Discovery is only reachable via pm_run action 'files-discover' (note param there). Fix options: route case 'files' to runFilesDiscover when options.discover===true (mapping discoveryNote->note, honoring apply/appendStable), or drop the three params from the files schema contract and document pm_run files-discover as the only path. Found 2026-06-12 while wiring pm-pfnx (--note/addNote)."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/type","value":"Issue"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/status","value":"open"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/priority","value":3},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/tags","value":["agent-ux","dogfood","mcp"]},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/created_at","value":"2026-06-11T22:13:41.473Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-06-11T22:13:41.473Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/author","value":"cli-fixes-agent"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/parent","value":"pm-mpbb"}],"before_hash":"3cc22dff72be7b14824654a7a64ea62b04799939b2fee54c1b5f52ca60bf6df0","after_hash":"249babc1cd7076b798ab63096e9d6aa235c70c527eba057377519298b1f2c0d4","message":""}
